            </fr:tree>
            <html:p>which is supposedly a "good" approximation of the data distribution <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q]]></fr:tex>. We can then show that a <html:em>conditional flow matching loss</html:em> has the same gradient as the full <html:em>flow matching loss</html:em> i.e. our vector field should converge to the <html:em>marginal vector field</html:em>, which is a good approximation for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[q]]></fr:tex>.
 </html:p>
